lead_paragraph: The missile fell far short of its estimated full range, but neither the United States nor South Korea immediately dismissed the test as a failure.

byline.contributor: Jane Perlez contributed reporting from Beijing and Jonathan Soble from Tokyo.

headline.print_headline: Missile Test by North Fails, South Korea Says
headline.main: North Korea Fires 2nd Missile After Earlier Test Fails

snippet: The missile fell far short of its estimated full range, but neither the United States nor South Korea immediately dismissed the test as a failure.
abstract: North Korea test-launches two Musudan intermediate-range ballistic missiles, one of which travels 250 miles before crashing into sea; test, while technically unsuccessful, achieves enough progress from previous failures to prompt South Korean officials to convene meeting; timing suggests North Korean leader Kim Jong-un is rushing to demonstrate his ability to strike American bases in Guam.
